# {{ project_name }} - Development Rules

## HTML Standards

### Semantic Markup
```html
<!-- Good -->
<header>, <nav>, <main>, <article>, <section>, <footer>

<!-- Avoid -->
<div class="header">, <div class="nav">
```

### Accessibility
- All images need `alt` attributes
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)
- Include ARIA labels where needed
- Ensure keyboard navigation works

## CSS Standards

{% if css_framework == 'vanilla' %}
### Naming Convention (BEM)
```css
.block {}
.block__element {}
.block--modifier {}

/* Example */
.card {}
.card__title {}
.card--featured {}
```

{% if use_css_variables %}
### Use CSS Variables
```css
/* Good */
color: var(--primary-color);

/* Avoid */
color: #2563eb;
```
{% endif %}
{% elif css_framework == 'tailwind' %}
### Tailwind Best Practices
- Use utility classes in HTML
- Extract components for repeated patterns
- Avoid custom CSS when utilities exist
{% elif css_framework == 'bootstrap' %}
### Bootstrap Best Practices
- Use Bootstrap classes before custom CSS
- Extend with custom utilities sparingly
- Follow Bootstrap's naming conventions
{% endif %}

### Mobile First
```css
/* Base styles for mobile */
.element { }

/* Then add breakpoints */
@media (min-width: 768px) { }
```

## JavaScript Standards

### Naming Conventions
```javascript
// Variables and functions: camelCase
const userName = 'John';
function getUserData() {}

// Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
const API_BASE_URL = '/api';

// Classes: PascalCase
class UserManager {}
```

{% if js_type == 'es6_modules' %}
### ES6 Modules
```javascript
// Named exports
export function helper() {}
export const CONFIG = {};

// Default export
export default class Main {}

// Imports
import { helper } from './utils.js';
```
{% endif %}

### Error Handling
```javascript
try {
    await fetchData();
} catch (error) {
    console.error('Error:', error);
    showUserMessage('Something went wrong');
}
```

## File Organization

### CSS Files
- `variables.css` - Design tokens only
- `style.css` - Component styles
- `responsive.css` - Media queries only

### JavaScript Files
- One purpose per file
- Export reusable functions
- Keep files under 200 lines

## Git Workflow

### Commit Messages
```
feat: Add navigation component
fix: Correct responsive breakpoints
style: Format CSS files
docs: Update README
```

